review_blob: This is just through and through a good solid beer.  The color, taste,palate are all exactly my style.  May not fit a classic profile, but its an outstanding example of exactly what it is.  Good stuff!

Nice crisp citrus orange aroma and start.  Finishes with a strong lingering bitterness that is complimentary.  This ipa avoids being overwhelming by the mellowing it receives aging on those Louisville sluggers.  Its definitely a hit.

My first time trying this local brew.  Great beer.  Not my usual preference but I found it easy to drink and refreshing.  A good beer for a day or night of casual drinking.  Smooth crisp and high quality beer.
This beer looks and tastes like a regular pilsner but gets extra points from me for the doubled ABV.  Nice sessionable yet strong beer.
